this review is written from the perspective of someone playing with all dlc take control of one of the most successful nations in history as their most successful leader and lead your people to become the greatest nation the world has ever seen civ 5 is one of the most popular and well known turnbased strategy games available on steam and its there for a reason with an unrivalled techtree attention to detail and variety this game has something for all strategy fans beautiful looking game complex tech tree challenging ai multiple paths to victory large variety of maps and game options youll never play the same game twice numerous nations to choose from great modding community especially for new maps great fun with friends but only at a similar skill level easy to learn hard to master a full match on normal difficulty takes upwards of five hours some nations are clearly more powerful than others it takes an incredibly long time to process computer turns when playing against a large number of nations in later stages of the game enemy nations can very quickly overwhelm others and gain large amounts of land the ai always have double standards especially when it comes to expanding borders on spying on one another verdict 9 an absolute must play for strategy fans el k
