you there are you able to steer every part of a budding nation to greatness do you want to squabble with other nations over resources like bananas and uranium are you able to deal with montezuma declaring war with you every fifteen turns or so can you stop that scheming  gandhi from nuking you to extinction if you answered yes to all or at least most of these questions then you should try out civilization v you wont be disappointed i havent played the other civilization games so im not sure how they compete but this game is certainly friendly to newcomers to the series the game is very intuitive and helps you keep the game moving by pointing out what you still need to do this turn before letting you move on to the next no more checking every unit and every city six times like in the total war games the game offers several options for victory you can simply kill em all you can send a spaceship to alpha centauri to prove your technological dominance you can make your civilisation the cultural center of the world or you can win through diplomacy by earning votes in the united nations that is as soon as you build it yes you theres several ways in which your civilization has to compete with their rivals theres luxury resources scattered across the map which are vital in keeping your empire happy theres strategic resources which are required to build certain units and buildings factories require coal for instance theres city states which will favor the most helpful or most generous civilization and grant them the earliermentioned resources and of course theres the everlasting race to keep your economy and military up to par with the other players each player is outfitted with a unique ai but you can also choose to randomize them to keep the game unpredictable all in all this game offers more strategies than countable what do you research first where do you send your new citizen to work where are you going to settle your new city how many cities do you need for your plan for world domination anyway will you build a wall to defend yourself or a library to speed up your research and so on tldr version plenty of tactics to be found here if you like turnbased strategy games this ones for you
