quick review sid meiers civilization v is one of the best strategy games i have ever played period i struggled to get into the medieval total war games however ive been playing the civilization games since i was twelveyearsold the game is rather expensive and to get all the achievements you need to get a fair amount of dlc i purchased civ5 gold edition so i was forced to also buy the brave new world dlc so fair warning if youre after everything expect the dlc trick detailed breakdown review story there are three main aspects to sid meiers civilization v 1 single player matches 2 single player scenarios 3 multiplayer matches as single player you may select from a list of nations to play as you may chose as rome greece germany the united states russia england and many others you play against other npcs you can choose your map size map style and other specialized options in the scenarios you are usually given a choice of nations that were in that scenario often times the scenarios are historic events such as the conquest of genghis khan 1066 conquest of england or the fall of rome lastly in multiplayer you can have a battle of wits against your friends you can play coop on the same computer or play online with your steam friends this mode is definitely an incentive for people whom are more competitive game play as ive elaborated already you can choose your country be sure to read the perks that country has certain countries are more effective at certain things some countries start out with special units others get bonuses from conquering barbarians and still others get great benefits from citystates the game has a lot to keep in mind while you play thankfully the game has advisors which help you get used to the game really fast they always pitch in their opinions and explain whats happening in the game are you an advanced player and tired of hearing them say the same things over and over no problem just disable them in the options menu in game you start with building your first city which becomes your capital and then you build armies settlers to build more cities workers buildings wonders and much much more achievements i wouldnt be consistent and true to my nature if i didnt add notes about achievements in my reviews lets face it many of the achievements in civ5 are a grind win as every nation play as every map size and type chop down 1000 tree tiles a lot of these achievements arent particularly interesting however i enjoyed them greatly and many people who might be looking to get away from grinding might prefer to avoid this game for the achievements alone many other achievements are very challenging to get at this time i havent started to work on getting deity the hardest difficulty achievements but many of those achievements are very difficult to get and often times require some tricks you pick up from playing price as i have already indicated expect this game to be rather pricy the vanilla original version of the game is $2999 if you are just looking to play a strategy game i think thats a fair price for the amount of time you can put into this game but to get more enjoyment out of your game the dlc does bring new scenarios new nations and new elements to the game that really makes the game just that more dynamic if you are looking for the whole set i would recommend buying the sid meiers civilization v complete edition its standard price is $4999 i would also recommend waiting for a price reduction either on christmas or the summer steam sale or keep your eyes open for a humble bundle sale conclusion while the game might be expensive i have personally put 219 hours into the game at this time for me thats the mark of a good game and having great replayability  if you enjoy playing it enough that you hit the 200 hours mark i have enjoyed the quality of the game the game style playing it with my friends and family and enjoyed getting the various achievements i highly recommend this game to anyone who has liked civilization games in the past and anyone who is looking for a strategy game to simply try out
