when i look for a strategy game im interested in three things i want a deep and rich strategy platform something that makes you think and really makes you feel like you are in control all decisions good or bad will way into the outcome of the game and only when you are at your best will you obtain victory i want this deep strategy but i also dont want it at the price of over complicating things too much of a good thing as they say it needs to have that deep strategy but not get overly complicated about it last and most obviously the game needs to be entertaining by this i mean that even if the game takes a while to complete as most strategy games do i want to enjoy the entire experience and not feel as though i am grinding through the game or spend unnecessary amounts of time just waiting for things to happen or finish happening civilization v hits this on all points with every expansion the way to victory has become deeper and more rewarding without getting unbalanced or to complicated everything is very intuitive without being too simple you really feel as though you are in control of a civ and building your way to global domination and victory civilization has always been one of the best strategy games out there and the latest instalment continues this tradition 9510
