recommended
civilization v it can be said without doubt that civilization v with all its expansions dlcs and addons is the most complete civilization game to date it possesses a great deal of strategic and tactical options but hidden deeper within its hulking playallofhumanhistory theme lay its greatest features it has character depth and charm that only further add to what is an astounding amount of replay value add steam workshop support and a robust modding community and you have a game that can truly stand the test of time i started my civilizationing while still in single digits age wise playing civ ii on the playstation and slowly matured into a more season tbs gamer with titles such as heroes of might and magic 3 when civilization iv was released i had just grown into the world of pc gaming and enjoyed at least a thousand hours of fun through hundreds of playthroughs when civilization v was announced i took time off work since i knew that i would be one more turn struck for several days the music art design ui  everything on the surface of this game is top notch from the sublime ability to switch from industrial production to artistic endeavours to the hardcore build orders used by veterans its all there the introduction of a hexagon grid simply makes sense and it would now seem ridiculous to ever return to square blocks military units are also no longer allowed to be stacked together into formidable doom stacks that conquer whole nations both of these changes force players to adapt to terrain and it requires great tactical and strategic skill both in the short and long term to outsmart another player small issues such as sometimes predictable ai and long turn times still plague the game though these issues are easy to overlook given the charm and fantastic design of civilization v do i recommend civilization v on its own sadly i do not but if you have the coin to purchase the complete edition of the game i couldnt recommend it enough tldr  buy it buy the expasions happy gaming friends
