if you are looking for a review you have come to the wrong place however i do have a very good casserole recipe these are the ingredients 1 pound dry ziti pasta 1 onion chopped 1 pound lean ground beef 2 26 ounce jars spaghetti sauce 6 ounces provolone cheese sliced 1 12 cups sour cream 6 ounces mozzarella cheese shredded 2 tablespoons grated parmesan cheese directions 1 bring a large pot of lightly salted water to a boil add ziti pasta and cook until al dente about 8 minutes drain 2 in a large skillet brown onion and ground beef over medium heat add spaghetti sauce and simmer 15 minutes 3 preheat the oven to 350 degrees f 175 degrees c butter a 9x13 inch baking dish layer as follows 12 of the ziti provolone cheese sour cream 12 sauce mixture remaining ziti mozzarella cheese and remaining sauce mixture top with grated parmesan cheese 4 bake for 30 minutes in the preheated oven or until cheeses are melted 5 take out of the oven and eat while hot
