recommended
for those who like the genre it is a stepup on the previous installments regarding obviously additional options especially with the 2 expansions gods and kings and brave new world the social policies changes and the introduction of religion options and citystates and interaction with said citystates were the biggest changes in the game in terms of different things to do that said i think theres still room for improvement on additional options you might have in terms of policy choosing etc the economy system is also a bit different from previous installments a bit richer and i think the military aspect of the game improved a lot in terms of tactics granted still room for improvement there but much less cheesy tactics like stacking 20 units in a tile for instance you now really need to know where to position your units and use choke points etc to your advantage much more chesslike than winbymorenumbers some of the different win conditions have also gained more depth especially the diplomatic  cultural victory the mods from the steam workshop are also insanely rich giving you even more customization  replay value to the game lastly the graphics have obviously also improved a lot with a lot more detail even though at least for me thats the least concerning aspect of a game such as this its downsides as usual mostly revolve around the need to have a sufficiently good pc to handle the burden of loading times etc as it is quite heavy on your pc most games also tend to have a midgame era which is quite stale where pretty much nothing happens regardless of whether youre far ahead far behind or even with the majority of the other civs ai is also something that still hasnt improved as much as i would have liked it is either too aggressive or too passive but not really playing intelligently regardless of difficulty level but rather as usual gaining more bonuses to make up fo the lack of actual intelligence on the artificial intelligence part so breaking it down pros  even more tech  social options richer interaction with citystates  religion now plays a big role in the game  more depth in cultural  diplomatic win conditions  improved combat  tactical aspect of the game  improved mod  customization in steam workshop  lots of replay value  better graphics cons  game can be quite the resourcehog on your pc regardless of having or not a good one  some games can turn out to be stale for quite some time depending on specific spawn points etc  could still have improved social policy choosing despite the huge improvements on that aspect  ais actual intelligence part hasnt really improved in my opinion tldr a solid 85 out of 10 whether youre new to the franchise or have played them all since the very first pixelated civilization 1 like myself would honestly give it more if the loading times were faster i dont mind putting in the hours playing the game its just a bit bothersome knowing that a somewhat significant part of those hours are spent waiting rather than playing
