i went into playing civ 5 with a grain of salt civ4 was my very first computer game and i remember being real excited when its sequel was announced when i looked at many of the reviews for this game they were very negative saying that it was dumbed down and bad i got this game and i started playing if you expect it to be a superhard strategy game well youre going to be disappointed but i dont think its dumbed down it feels just like civ4 there are a couple new mechanics though none of them really effect gameplay in a big way however its still just as easy and entertaining as 4 the gameplay is simple which i found particularly nice considering that learning new mechanics would mess with my civ4 habits and yet is very engaging i started playing this worried whether ot not itd be worth it at about 1820 i stopped playing it at 2000 i felt like i was playing civ4 with more countries and some new features all in all civ5 no matter what you here is worth the money it has scenarios that i havent even delved into yet in my opinion they were one of the best part of 4 and warlords and plenty of mod support the graphics obviously are much better which gives you something a little prettier to look at as you build your country so what are you waiting for buy it actually buy civ4 first and then buy this
