addicting thats my oneword concept for this review sid meiers civilization v is addicting its like a drug you try it for the first time and you like it a little and tell yourself i can quit any time i want then a week and 5 civ sessions later you find yourself spouting the games mantra just one more turn the gameplay is fun and inviting in the early stages of the game lack of proper preparation can get you killed on the harder difficulty levels but its pretty forgiving on the easier difficulties and there is something oh so satisfying about ruling an entire empire especially in the later portions of the game when you have the entire world at your fingertips the graphics are much improved over previous iterations of the game the new hexagon tile system works better than the old square based system as well the ai is also better though still frustratingly simpleminded the amount of times theyve declared war on me for the simple act of making friends with other citystates is astounding speaking of citystates are a worthwhile entry into the series they add an entire new element giving you someone to barter with or an extra thorn in your side depending on how you play the game they can mostly be manipulated at will but the ease with which an enemy civilization can bring them into a war effort against you can be alarming most of the time they dont factor into a war very much but occasionally they will send out a unit to battle overall this game is fun inventive and rewarding to play but all of that only really tells you one thing this game is addictive
