gameplay 55 builds stress at all the right times and certain ai add extra flavor graphics 45 takes a bit of time and tinkering to run smoothly and your computer definitely will get a little toasty but this is made up for by the stunning amount of resources the game can handle at once design 55 the devil is in the details and civ is packed with bells and whistles on every tile the ui can appear daunting at first but in the long run becomes incredibly simplistic sound 45 the score and narration really enhance the immersion and make your civilizations story all the more epic multiplayer 35 the only aspect of the game that is just average the graphics and amount of ai the game can handle take a significant blow in multiplayer and the way the game freezes entirely if youre at war with another player and its their turn can be frustrating the lack of achievement support in multiplayer is also a bit disappointing pc factor 55 the mod support is absolutely fantastic and propels this game to be a staple of pc gaming replay factorachievements 55 by the end of one really long game you will have a full understanding of how to play and be ready to rack up another hundred hours over the course of two days this game will make you think thats possible civilization v is the kind of game that may lead you to rehab but thatll only hurt your loved ones and youre two turns away from learning how to build a giant atomic robot so who cares overall 89
