i have not played many hours of civ 5 but i would like to give my intial thoughts and views on this game i would like to start by comparing this game to a board game think catan with a little bit of risk moved in now that you can view it as this now add in a little of age of empires this is a turned based version of these gamesboard games are usually turned based the atmosphere is great and the initail game i played had me stuck for 6 hours straight this game is very good as it keeps you stuck in for the long haul the objectives in the game are great as there is more than one way to win you can build a giant army and march across the battlefeild crushing your enemys going the cultural root and increasing your artistic side of the city this gives the game varity and replayability the diffrent racesworld leaders you can choose from also gives the game a great uniqueness that allows for hours of gameplay there is no story there is just advance you civilisation 5 to the best point by researching diffrent things and building unique buildings from throughout history there is a multiplayer that i have not yet delved into i believe the multiplayer would increase the game time by at least another 23 hours i have an estimation that each game on normal of about 68 hours this game takes some thinking and a few of the actions take a while to figure out this game is very good at explaining what you have to do to learn how to play from what i have played so far i would say this is a very great game and has given me the longest single sitting in anygame i have played in for a very very long time well worth a look at the time of this review the game and the dlc is avalible on humblebundlecom for $15 as well as some other games
