sid meiers civilization v is one of the best additions to my steam library ever at the moment im roughly a bit more than 200 hours into the game which is personally a lot of time for me and i still play several turns each week pros  [laptops] does not require a mouse playable on the go i frequently travel by train and whenever it takes a while i grab my laptop and fire up civ  a large variety of civilizations to toy with even more when you purchase dlc and expansion packs with each their unique buildings units and traits  four speed options for the patient and less patient ones me i tried marathon mode big mistake but my ocd kicked in and i just had to finish it  a large amount of mechanics the game is complex but its a great once you get the hang of everything  for those who crave knowledge the game gives accurate information about the civilizations units and buildings  playable on tablets cons  might feel repetitive for some  noobunfriendly imo i wouldnt try playing on normal mode prince or online if youre not familiar to civ or the strategy genre  time consuming be prepared to lose a lot of time playing this game and maybe some sleep once you get hooked  waging war with an ai on lower difficulty levels may be very boring and feel ridiculously easy its common knowledge among players that the ai is terrible naval warfare conclusion civlization v is not a game for those who crave intense action and immediate results civ v is for those who like to put their brain to work and play that chesslike one step ahead way where a grave error can actually screw up your whole game to the strategists out there id highly recommend the game and its certainly worth its price i avoid rating simply because a rating mostly doesnt do anything justice a tip dont buy games or watch films just based on a rating and actually read reviews if you wish to consider something you might bump into lots of cool things that are supposedly considered bad though if i were to actually rate civ id say a 9510 nb i mentioned as one of the pros that civilization is playable on tablets normally this is not possible if you have an android tablet or ipad but there is a way to stream your pc to a tablet using splashtop which is available for both anrdoid and apple products there are several guides available online on how to do this
