a very unique game sid meiers civilization v civ v is a 4x video game in the civilization series developed by firaxis games released on microsoft windows in september 2010 when it comes down to it civ v is a turn based strategy game the basic idea of a civilization game is to have the best civilization compared to your neighboring civilizations how you do that can be done in a few ways my first and favorite method is by complete domination of other civs what ill do is grow my civilization expand my borders and declare war on anyone thats a threat to me and my borders or simply to pick on the weak or expand my own territory and civilization as technology within my civilization progresses they go through different eras such the ones listed here ancient era classical era medieval era renaissance era industrial era modern era atomic era information era etc at first my army will just be a bunch of barbarians with axes archers catapaults etc but then as my technology advances eventually ill have modern era soldiers with rifles tanks aircraft and nuclear bombs i just have to be sure not to fall behind on the tech tree or else ill get destoryed by somone with a far more advanced army with guns while i still have axes ultimately ill have to conquer every civilizations original capital city to beat the game although if i dont conquer them fast enough then i may lose to another civ by means of other victory types how well other victory methods may not even regard any combat whatsoever you can have the best civilization with the best culturetourism knowledge of science be the first to launch a spaceship diplomacy or overall score if the time runs out etc i cant speak for these victory types since i always go for the domination path the maps in civ v are generated by random and offer plenty of variety every time and even if thats not enough than the modding community has you covered theyll have you covered with many other things as well such as custom guis unit skins stastitics etc i cant speak for multiplayer i prefer this time consuming game alone but speaking of time consuming civ v could take as long as a whole day or more just to complete one game but dont let that scare you off just save your game and pick up where you left off next time although there is plenty of customization that can be done in terms of settings to make the game speed faster or much longer as well as make the overall difficulty harder or gameplay more interesting if youre new to civilization games then this game is not newb friendly out of my 130 hours ive only won about 4 times out of plenty of games but that goes to show you that even if i lose civ is a fun addicting experience but for all players no matter the skill level i highly reccomend this site for a guidance httpwwwcarlsguidescomstrategycivilization5 also be sure to pick up civ v complete and not just civ v the base game its worth it
