out of all my steam games this is the one game i keep coming back to when it was first released i truly hated it it was a rushed and broken game now it has become one of my alltime favourite games the turn based nature of this game means you get the time to plan your empire and diplomatic strategy battles can become large chesslike conflicts that require you to look at the bigger picture  simple numbers will not win you a fight unless on the easiest difficulty of course the game is engaging with a gigantic tech tree to keep you interested there are also numerous scenarios to choose from such as the fall of rome and the american civil war you can also fully customise your game and create your own scenarios for you and your friends to play the vanilla game is massive and will keep you occupied for many an hour trying to crush bribe sleaze or geek your way to victory then there is the added bonus of the workshop turning this already huge game into an endless life sucking monster from which there is no return in all i love this game and if you like turn based strategy games this is definitely one you need in your collection
