what can i say civ 5 is my favorite game well at least for now any way i am a big strategy game fan and most civ games suit my expectations about what i look for in a turn based strategy games but civ 5 is the best out of all of them right now in my opinion so far i have 122 hours clocked in on this game and that number will be sure to grow words cant describe how fun it is to start off as an ancient civilization starting out with nothing and slowly grow over time expanding and conquering your foes civ 5 will bring fun to the table for hours now there are issues with the game as in any games like how i think the diplomacy in this game is horrible compared to civ 4 and the location of rescourses and what kind and how much spawns in any one game but the combat system is way better unlike in previous instalments in civ 5 you dont have to go attack with dumb death stacks that actually take away from any kind of militaristic strategies i also noticed that in late game when anti air units come into play they dont always tend to work the civilopidea doesnt give enough info and it lacks some basic tips when hovering the cursor over certain things but these issues are very minor and dont detract from the fun of the game at all like i said ive clocked in countless hours of this game so far and feel i have the right to review the game now and i give it a thumbs up 9 out of 10 if youve never played a civ game and are interested or you just love turn based strategy civ 5 s the best place to start for newbies and vets alike just make sure you buy the complete eddition for the highest extent of fun
