civ 5 took a while to grow on me on its first release i was not impressed the expansion packs have really added a lot though and i think with time i also got over the differences as compared to civ 4 im really torn on the gameiness of civ 5 though like i still feel like the social policy trees and the citystates dont naturally fit theyre fun because youre leveling up and questing but the policy system of civ 4 seemed like it made more sense from a simulation point of view and gave you some cool flexibility when your needs changed and the city state quests quickly become stupid and again feel more like gimmicky game elements rather than a part of history but again the policies are rewarding and the revamped cultural victory introduced in brave new world moves them from gimmicks supporting a weird win condition to fun ways to customize your game i could still do without the city states though i agree that the diplomatic victory from previous games was poorly done and i appreciate that city states do fix this but it seems like a poorer fix than might have been hoped on a sidenote id be curious to play vanilla civ 5 and see if it still feels weak compared to vanilla civ 4 or if my resistance to civ 5 really was just eew hexes and nonstacked units  weird either way i have since come to really enjoy civ 5 especially with brave new world i look forward to civ 6 whatever shape it may take unless its online only thank god civ isnt owned by ea
