civilization v is not as advanced as titles such as europa universalis and such what it is  though is perhaps the most accesible grand strategy games on the marketit has tutorials that will ease you into the game quickly and it manages to be understandable and extremely fun for even people new to the series the game allows you to play the game how you want you can make a game short or long depending on the amount of time you want to sink in and youll want to sink in even though i said it is dumbed down compared to paradox interactive titles there is still a hell of a lot to do  not even counting the two massive expansions although i think the game does feel less engaging without the expansions so id highly recommend getting them the inclusion of the steam workshop is a nice touch  but not especially new since civ games since 2  have always had the option of user created content when you dive into the game  after picking a map  a civ 43 with all dlc  and a speed there are also advanced options which allow you to tweak game settings and spice up the experience like a onecity challenge youll experience the building of your empire from 4000bc to the future youll declare war on other civs or you might engage in trading  or maybe youll enact a research agreement so you can unlock rifling or whatever else with the two expansions added a whole new element of diversity is added as you spread religion and tourism spy on your enemies and friends  ultilitize trade caravans vote on world issues and advancements in the world congress  and pick your civilizations ideology  each expansion gameplay system grants benefits to the player and deeply increases the fun of the early and middlelate game periods city statessmall civs in short are included in vanilla and expanded upon in the expansions which allow you to use them for your economic militaristic or cultural benefit honestly  there is so much to do  i could go on for days do note that the ai and diplomacy is severely better in the expansions so i would defintely recommend them too multiplayer is apparently good too  although i havent played much of that civ 5 is hard to sum up in one word i could write ten articles  but ill have to settle with fantastic
