i played a lot of civilization 4 back in the day with my brother and went into this one kind of expecting the same thing big mistake  theyve streamlined some of the annoying things like limiting your resources instead of having unlimited supplies  theyve improved the combat side by removing the stacking of units on a single tile and steam rolling over everything  theyve also removed the need to build transports for continent naval invasion which for me is a major plus point the downside however  with the streamlining process is the lack of control over the finer details  you cant select all your cities on the same content to mass produce units or buildings anymore  you cant pull up a chart summarizing all the nations power or overall growth overall it is definitely a step in right direction but it lost a lot useful things along the way 810
